<h2 class="learn-heading">Learn: Marker Usage for a Momentary Behavior</h2>

<p>Most of the things we want our dogs to do are quick, momentary behaviors. For the most part there are two outcomes:</p>

<ul class="list-disc list-inside my-4 space-y-2">
  <li><strong>They do it</strong>: Mark with terminal marker ("yes"), reward.</li>
  <li><strong>They don't do it</strong>: Feedback marker ("nope"), try again. Remember, "nope" is totally optional. If you say "yes" for everything good, they will learn the game eventually.</li>
</ul>

<p>It's still as easy as we learned. The only difference is that we can now optionally use our feedback marker ("nope") to help guide them. Let me show you an example with "sit."</p>

