    <h2>The Bigger Picture</h2>
    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 mb-6">WHY ARE WE DOING THIS?</p>

    <p class="mb-4">Implied stay changes everything. Instead of saying "sit... sit... SIT... STAY," you simply say "sit" once and your dog knows to hold that position until released. This is how professional trainers work with their dogs.</p>

    <p class="mb-4">The release word is equally important. Dogs who are released from every command learn to wait for permission before acting. This builds impulse control and makes them easier to live with in every way.</p>

